Design a URL shortening service like TinyURL or Bitly with the following requirements:

Functional Requirements:

Given a long URL, the system should generate a short URL.
Given a short URL, the system should redirect to the original long URL.
The short URL should be unique.
Support custom short alias (optional) — user can provide their own short string.
Support expiration of short URLs (optional but good to discuss).

Non-Functional Requirements:

The service should be highly available and scalable (handle millions of URLs and high redirection traffic).
Redirection should be very fast (low latency).
Short URLs should be as short as possible (ideally 7-8 characters).

Out of Scope (for basic LLD):

User authentication / analytics dashboard
Advanced security (malicious URL detection)
Click analytics with charts

